output as 'features-sections.html' and 'features.css'.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"develop-shop\",\n      \"description\": \"Implement the shop section with product cards, pricing, and 'Add to Cart' buttons; use responsive grid layout; output as 'shop-section.html' and 'shop.css'.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"integrate-page\",\n      \"description\": \"Combine all HTML and CSS files into a single responsive landing page, validate accessibility and cross-browser compatibility; deliver final 'index.html' and 'style.css' in 'dist/' folder.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n\n## Your Job\nFor EACH subtask in the plan:\n1. Pick the BEST matching template from the available templates above\n2. Optionally EDIT the system_prompt to add task-specific details (file names, specific requirements)\n3. Select a SUBSET of tools from the available tool menu that the worker needs\n4. Set skill_paths from the template\n\n## Rules\n- Output ONLY valid JSON — no markdown fences, no extra text\n- worker_name MUST match a template name (or be \"tester\")\n- system_prompt: start from the template prompt, then add task-specific instructions\n- tool_names: only pick from the available tool menu\n- skill_paths: copy the template's skill_paths or leave empty\n\n## Output Format\n{\n  \"workers\": [\n    {\n      \"worker_name\": \"template_name\",\n      \"system_prompt\": \"Full customized system instructions for the worker\",\n      \"tool_names\": [\"tool1\", \"tool2\"],\n      \"skill_paths\": [\"path/to/skill.json\"]\n    }\n  ]\n}", "meta": {}}
